Acquisition report
User acquisition report provides insights into how new users find your website or app for the first time, and help you understand the user profiles and user growth trends.

FormatText.RichText:
1 means engaged session of which duration >= 10s or contains >=2 views. 
0 means bounced session fo which duration < 10s or contain < 2 view.

TextBoxes.Content:
Engagement report
User engagement report provides metrics based on sessions and views that your users trigger when they are using with your apps to help you understand their engagement level.

FormatText.RichText: <visual-subtitle>You can search individual event and view its dimension and parameter details in this table. Click on the 'event_id' to view the event attributes. </visual-subtitle>

<visual-title>
  <inline font-size="16px">Top screen/page by average engagement time</inline>
</visual-title>

TextBoxes.Content:
Activity report
Y ou can use the Activity report to get insights into the activities the users performed when using your websites and apps. This report measures user activity by the events that users triggered, and let you view the detail attributes of the events.

FormatText.RichText: <visual-subtitle>Based on events in the selected period.</visual-subtitle>

<visual-title>
  <inline font-size="16px">User retention rate by returning days</inline>
</visual-title>

TextBoxes.Content:
Retention report
You can use the Retention report to get insights into how frequently the users engage with your website or mobile app after their first visit.

Device report
Device report helps you understand what device your users user to access your apps.

FormatText.RichText: <visual-subtitle>You can search individual event and view its dimension and parameter details in this table. Click on the 'event_id' to view the event attributes. </visual-subtitle>
<visual-subtitle>Note that user attribute data is updated once per day by default, you might see some users do not have attributes.</visual-subtitle>
<visual-subtitle>A table contains all user detail information for user to search and filter, useful when you need to focus on one specific user.</visual-subtitle>

User report
This report allows you to query and view individual user' attributes and the events the user performed.
